# Note that Pandas does not complain if we have duplicate index values in the DataFrame. However, it is generally recommended to have unique index values in a DataFrame to avoid any potential issues with data manipulation and analysis. If we have duplicate index values, it can lead to unexpected results when performing operations on the DataFrame, such as selecting specific rows or performing groupby operations. Therefore, it is important to ensure that the index of a DataFrame has unique values to maintain the integrity of the data and avoid any potential issues with data manipulation and analysis.